  and you just took the ride?

34:24.342 --> 34:26.677
didn't even know
what it was about?
he wasn't.

34:26.677 --> 34:28.929
he died trying to help me.

34:28.929 --> 34:34.518
if i should've signed my name
or took the drugs in myself,

34:34.518 --> 34:36.938
that's on me.

34:36.938 --> 34:39.739
don't do that to him.

34:48.748 --> 34:52.036
see, that is blackmail.
i know you talked to the judge.
relax, lisa.

34:52.036 --> 34:55.289
if you're making lonny the trick
on the complaint against me,
that is a joke.

34:55.289 --> 34:58.042
shut your mouth, lisa,
and we'll straighten this out.
i want out!

34:58.542 --> 35:00.544
i'm supposed to see
my girlfriend!

35:00.544 --> 35:03.431
what you want to do on the
outside can probably happen, but
first you do something for us.

35:03.431 --> 35:06.884
i showed you where to find
oswaldo. i did something
for you yesterday.

35:09.887 --> 35:13.140
lisa, we picked up
a guy last night.
someone dropped a dime,

35:13.140 --> 35:17.478
heard him talking in a bar
how him and a buddy
whacked a guy in a bodega.

35:17.895 --> 35:21.115
- uh-uh. forget it. no way.
- we just want you to look
  at this guy in a lineup.

35:21.115 --> 35:23.067
no way.
i wouldn't recognize him.

35:23.067 --> 35:25.903
no one's going to ask you
to testify, lisa.
you didn't see the shooting.

35:25.903 --> 35:28.572
we just want to know:
did you bang this guy
in the basement?

35:28.572 --> 35:31.459
i didn't bang anyone, okay?
i can prove i had
a female situation!

35:31.459 --> 35:35.913
whatever you did
in the basement.
no! no! no way!

35:35.913 --> 35:39.300
why don't you talk to oswaldo
instead of jamming me up.
you talk to that asshole lonny.

35:39.300 --> 35:43.304
- lonny didn't see nothing.
- well, i didn't either.

35:43.304 --> 35:46.974
i don't want
to make an i.d.

35:51.679 --> 35:54.015
gentlemen.

35:54.015 --> 35:56.067
[ fancy ] charge fat cat
and the two shooters
on the homicide.

35:56.567 --> 35:59.236
on the drug note,
we think the super's
telling the truth.

35:59.737 --> 36:01.605
meaning one corrupt cop minimum.

36:02.106 --> 36:04.108
[ fancy ] that part doesn't
work out of this office.
i.a.b. and the 27.

36:04.108 --> 36:05.860
and it don't give you no reason
to get in bed with fat cat.

36:05.860 --> 36:07.945
be interesting to hear
who was on his payroll.

36:07.945 --> 36:11.248
looks to piggyback
one case on the other...

36:11.248 --> 36:14.085
to get a bigger splash
for his boss,
this greasy little twerp.

36:14.085 --> 36:17.755
-don't bring it
 into this office.
-how do i get to be the bad guy?

36:17.755 --> 36:20.841
ask your parents.

36:20.841 --> 36:23.377
hi. you called in
that mrs. torrence
and her daughter?

36:23.377 --> 36:26.013
uh, yeah. yeah.
do this with me.

36:31.185 --> 36:33.137
mrs. torrence.

36:33.137 --> 36:37.608
when there's developments
in a case we try to let
you know about them.

36:38.109 --> 36:39.977
have there been arrests?
there have been, yes.

36:39.977 --> 36:43.364
we've arrested two men
we believe did
the actual shootings,

36:43.364 --> 36:47.201
and we put a warrant
out for a man
we think gave the order.

36:47.702 --> 36:49.787
his lawyer's
bringing him in.

36:49.787 --> 36:53.574
why did you accuse my brother
of being involved again?

36:53.574 --> 36:57.128
we were verifying that he
wasn't involved. sometimes
you take interview techniques,

36:57.128 --> 36:59.497
you make it seem that you
think something that you don't.

36:59.497 --> 37:02.216
taking his word would've been
out of the question.

37:02.216 --> 37:04.385
under these circumstances,
yes, it would have, ma'am.

37:05.586 --> 37:07.805
excuse me.

37:07.805 --> 37:10.591
we wanted to tell you
about the arrest,

37:10.591 --> 37:14.261
and we understood
and appreciated what
kwasi's role had been.

37:14.261 --> 37:17.898
yesterday hanna said
she believed that
her dad was a hero,

37:17.898 --> 37:20.484
and that's what our
investigation proved.

37:20.484 --> 37:25.189
[ clears throat ]
what it's worth, uh,
i had some respect for him too.

37:25.656 --> 37:29.243
he could've jammed me up
on this job when him and me
got into it,

37:29.243 --> 37:33.531
but he said his piece
to me man-to-man
and left it there.

37:33.531 --> 37:36.117
- can we go?
-i'd also say to hanna...

37:36.617 --> 37:41.922
it's hard to lose a dad before
his time, 'cause that happened
with my son,

37:41.922 --> 37:44.625
and i'm sorry
for you on that score.

37:45.126 --> 37:47.428
you just remember that's the man
who called your father a nigger.

37:47.428 --> 37:50.548
please,
don't say that to her.

37:50.548 --> 37:54.018
it, uh--
it was circumstances that
i think you know about,

37:54.018 --> 37:57.805
but i don't think she
could understand that.

37:57.805 --> 38:00.391
i don't ever want her
to understand someone
using that word.

38:00.891 --> 38:02.943
you called him a nigger.

38:02.943 --> 38:06.280
are you a bigot
and a hypocrite too?
i apologize then.

38:06.280 --> 38:09.900
people who hated him alive
don't get to say
nice things now.

38:09.900 --> 38:12.620
hanna, i--

38:12.620 --> 38:18.292
i apologize for using
that word about your father.

38:20.711 --> 38:23.130
all right.

38:52.159 --> 38:55.696
i'm leonard moscoso,
oswaldo mendoza's attorney.

38:55.696 --> 38:58.749
i thought moscoso's his doctor.
i believe felix moscoso
is his doctor.

38:59.250 --> 39:01.202
mr. mendoza's ill
and can't look at your lineup.

39:01.702 --> 39:04.455
yeah? can we bring him
a photo array?
at present, he's too ill.

39:04.455 --> 39:07.842
he can make the i.d.'s off the
record if he wants. we'll go
at these guys a different way.

39:07.842 --> 39:11.262
- we want an indication we're
  looking at the right people.
- mm-mm. too ill.

39:11.262 --> 39:15.216
so how come he picked up
the phone at home when
we asked him to come in?

39:15.216 --> 39:18.135
people don't have to be
in hospitals to be sick.

39:18.135 --> 39:21.388
we're gonna have to kick
this guy who could've
given up his accomplice.

39:21.388 --> 39:24.024
two murderers your client
can get off the streets. we're
gonna have to turn 'em loose.

39:24.024 --> 39:27.027
don't pretend your client
oswaldo wasn't working drug
deals out of that bodega,

39:27.027 --> 39:29.980
mr. moscoso,
not with that grocery selection.

39:29.980 --> 39:33.534
as long as you're running
errands, you tell oswaldo
he's a lying, gutless scumbag.

39:33.534 --> 39:36.620
it's easy to have opinions not
having to live and do business
in the neighborhood.

39:36.620 --> 39:38.989
my opinions don't depend
where i live.

39:38.989 --> 39:41.742
tell him he's a scumbag,
and he gets the neighborhood
he deserves.

39:41.742 --> 39:43.577
good day.
good day.

39:43.577 --> 39:46.497
hey, how's it going?
good.
how's yourself?

39:46.497 --> 39:48.499
all right.

39:48.999 --> 39:51.635
i guess we gotta
go kick this guy.

39:51.635 --> 39:53.888
[ hand thuds ]

40:01.262 --> 40:05.266
did you hear her
tell that little girl
to hate me?

40:05.766 --> 40:07.768
yeah.

40:13.274 --> 40:15.776
come back from vietnam,

40:15.776 --> 40:18.779
i go right on the job.

40:18.779 --> 40:22.283
job don't send me
to the academy or nothing.

40:22.283 --> 40:26.787
puts me undercover right away,
'cause-- cause i'm who
they're looking for.

40:26.787 --> 40:30.291
just out of the service,
working-class guy--

40:30.291 --> 40:35.296
all the credentials for being
some disillusioned asshole who
wants to piss on everything...

40:35.296 --> 40:39.800
i just spent
two and a half years
getting shot at about.

40:39.800 --> 40:43.804
i don't even get
to be with cops
when i'm debriefed.

40:43.804 --> 40:46.523
some guy in the bottom
of the post office building...

40:46.523 --> 40:49.526
takes my information
and tells me what to do.

40:50.027 --> 40:53.314
jerk in a suit--
he don't even tell me his name.

40:53.314 --> 40:55.733
he has me join
the young patriots.

40:55.733 --> 40:59.987
it's-- it's like
the women's auxiliary
for the black panthers.

40:59.987 --> 41:05.459
i get to bring
the panthers coffee
and lead cheers.

41:05.459 --> 41:08.963
"right on," you know.
"oh, you said a mouthful,
 brother."

41:08.963 --> 41:11.915
"let's definitely take
 that bank off."

41:13.917 --> 41:16.420
then i go work my cover job
unloading furniture.

41:16.920 --> 41:21.925
and then i go home and i drink
myself stupid so as not to run
my head into the wall,

41:21.925 --> 41:23.677
thinking how much i hate
what i'm doing.

41:23.677 --> 41:28.065
i sat in rice paddies the night
so dark you didn't know
which way was up,

41:28.565 --> 41:32.653
wanting to scream and shoot
your gun off for light and you'd
know where the hell you were,

41:32.653 --> 41:37.441
so i could come home and do
chores and hear my country get
pissed on by a bunch of spades!

41:37.441 --> 41:41.328
hey, andy!
don't start talking like that,
all right?

41:43.614 --> 41:45.866
i'm trying to explain
something to you.

41:45.866 --> 41:49.036
and i'm telling you
that when you use
that kind of language,

41:49.036 --> 41:52.256
i can't get to
what you're saying.

41:52.256 --> 41:54.758
you don't have
to call 'em spades
to tell what happened.

41:54.758 --> 41:58.345
- spades is how i feel.
- you call that
  little girl a spade?

41:58.345 --> 42:00.014
she's not who
i was talking about.

42:00.014 --> 42:03.350
well, that's who i see
when you're talking.
you follow my problem?

42:03.350 --> 42:06.470
hey, forget about it.
you have a nice night.

42:06.470 --> 42:09.356
i was trying to explain
something to you.
excuse me for--

42:09.356 --> 42:12.142
for trying to talk
to my partner.

42:12.142 --> 42:13.894
[ scoffs ]

42:15.779 --> 42:19.233
go ahead, partner.

42:19.233 --> 42:22.736
[ sniffs ]
it was hard for me.
you understand that, huh?

42:22.736 --> 42:26.740
come back to the world--
least i-- i thought i could
talk to somebody,

42:26.740 --> 42:30.461
and maybe somebody, uh,
respects what i did.

42:30.461 --> 42:32.629
i dreamt of being a cop.

42:32.629 --> 42:36.633
now a cop sees me
on the street he spits--
he spits on the ground.

42:36.633 --> 42:40.137
and i know he's supposed to,
'cause i'm kissing
bastards' asses...

42:40.137 --> 42:44.007
want to blow up the bank
that my mother pays
her house loans at.

42:44.007 --> 42:48.011
and i'm telling these bastards
how brave and great
i think they are.

42:48.011 --> 42:51.231
how i loved it when my dad--
he-he finally saved enough...

42:51.732 --> 42:54.234
after he's in the service
to move us from the quonsets.

42:54.735 --> 42:57.488
and we're finally
in a decent neighborhood
until they move in.

42:57.488 --> 43:01.692
i gotta fight to keep
my lunch money, and the project
turns into a sty.

43:01.692 --> 43:04.695
and he gets his eye put out
by one of 'em drunk
with a hammer...

43:04.695 --> 43:07.915
who don't want
his gas meter read.

43:10.084 --> 43:14.922
to have her tell
that little girl to hate me--

43:16.423 --> 43:18.425
i try to do my job.

43:18.425 --> 43:22.429
put your own feelings aside
unless they show you
they're wrong.

43:22.429 --> 43:26.216
and that sweet little girl
is told to hate me.

43:26.216 --> 43:31.305
but what is she supposed to do,
andy? she supposed to feel
sorry for you?

43:31.805 --> 43:34.308
she's supposed to think
it's okay you call
her father a nigger...

43:34.308 --> 43:36.560
because you had
bad times growing up?

43:36.560 --> 43:40.647
i had bad times from them people
my whole life.

43:41.648 --> 43:43.650
hey, my dad got his ass kicked
at shape-ups...

43:44.151 --> 43:46.987
by white longshoremen
for being dark-skinned.

43:47.488 --> 43:51.959
i don't hate them people,
and i don't hate you.

43:51.959 --> 43:56.914
but i'm supposed to care
what happened to her people
300 years ago.

43:58.916 --> 44:00.717
there you go.

44:03.086 --> 44:05.088
at least she shook my hand.

44:06.089 --> 44:07.925
yeah.

44:09.393 --> 44:11.895
i don't think
she hated me that much.

44:21.822 --> 44:24.158
[ door closes ]

